 who became Dallas' most notorious jewel thief; and Katy Vine tracks a pair of teenage lesbians inspired by Thelma and Louise. Texas Monthly On. Texas True Crime is the second in a series of books in which the editors of Texas Monthly offer the magazine's inimitable perspective on various aspects of Texas culture, including food, politics, travel, and music, among other topics. Texas Monthly On. Texas Women was released in 2006.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCrimezTexasvCase studies. 0aCriminalszTexasvCase studies. 7aTRUE CRIME / General.2bisacsh1 aBallí, Cecilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColloff, Pamela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHollandsworth, Skip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Evan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Evan.1 aVine, Katy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292795532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292795532/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK